  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Hey everybody! (well, everybody on the OpenHatch bug tracker ^_^ )

We are currently in the middle of setting up a fancy new central login system so
that you only need to login once to access the main site, wiki and bug tracker;
this bug is purely about making sure that you all know what is happening. The
central login system being developed keeps track of a single person across the
multiple authentication systems via their username, and if anyone's usernames in
the different databases are different at time of switch-on, they will lose
access to those accounts and new ones with the same username as the main site
will be created, resulting in loss of user-bug information etc.

So we would like to ask everyone to ensure that their Roundup login name is the
same as their main OpenHatch username. This should only take about a minute of
your time, and will greatly help us make smooth transition to the unified login
system. If you find that your Roundup login name needs changing, simply follow
the link in the banner or the bottom of the sidebar to your details page to do
so. (And if you can't remember your OpenHatch username,
<a href="http://openhatch.org/account/login/">http://openhatch.org/account/login/</a> can help you with that =D )

Cheers,
Jack Grigg</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
